Sentencas: A reactive element layer is introduced into the coating system to enhance the properties of FeCoNi coating for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects.
Titulo: Efficient FeCoNi/CeO2 coatings for solid oxide fuel cell steel interconnect applications

Sentencas: An FeCoNi/CeO2 dual-layer coating is produced on stainless steel by sol-gel and magnetron sputtering, which is subsequently exposed to 800 degrees C for a duration of up to 20 weeks.
Titulo: Efficient FeCoNi/CeO2 coatings for solid oxide fuel cell steel interconnect applications

Sentencas: The thermal treatment results in the formation of (Fe,Co,Ni)3O4 spinel and (Ni,Co)O, with CeO2 embedded in Cr2O3 that formed beneath the spinel.
Titulo: Efficient FeCoNi/CeO2 coatings for solid oxide fuel cell steel interconnect applications

Sentencas: The FeCoNi/CeO2 coating demonstrates better effectiveness than FeCoNi coating in acting as a barrier against Cr out-diffusion.
Titulo: Efficient FeCoNi/CeO2 coatings for solid oxide fuel cell steel interconnect applications

Sentencas: Moreover, adding CeO2 significantly suppresses the interfacial reaction of Cr2O3 and spinel.
Titulo: Efficient FeCoNi/CeO2 coatings for solid oxide fuel cell steel interconnect applications

Sentencas: An area-specific resistance of 10 mil cm2 is obtained for the FeCoNi/CeO2 coated steel at 800 degrees C after 20 weeks.
Titulo: Efficient FeCoNi/CeO2 coatings for solid oxide fuel cell steel interconnect applications
